Define $c_{1}$ and $p_{1}$ as the values of the call and the put when the volatility is $\sigma_{1}$. Define $c_{2}$ and $p_{2}$ as the values of the call and the put when the volatility is $\sigma_{2}$. From put-call parity

$$
\begin{aligned}
& p_{1}+S_{0} e^{-q T}=c_{1}+K e^{-r T} \\
& p_{2}+S_{0} e^{-q T}=c_{2}+K e^{-r T}
\end{aligned}
$$

If follows that

$$
p_{1}-p_{2}=c_{1}-c_{2}
$$

